article.headline: Dayton 67, South Carolina State 55
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Monty Scott scored 19 points and Brian Roberts added 17 points and six assists Tuesday to lead Dayton to a 67-55 win over South Carolina State. The Flyers (5-1) pulled to a 27-19 lead by the half and were ahead by as much as 21 points during the second period. The Bulldogs (0-5) never had the lead. The closest they came was an 11-11 tie about halfway through the first period. Travis Jones led South Carolina State in scoring with 16 points. Brian Mason scored 10 and Jason Flagler added eight points and eight rebounds. Charles Little added 11 points and Kurt Huelsman had eight points and eight rebounds for the Flyers, who shot 49 percent overall to the Bulldogs' 40 percent.
